Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Burghill was born about 1346, in Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Thomas Burghill II, was 18 and his mother, Sybil Hursley, was 14. He married Peryn  'Perinda' Walwyn in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. He died in his hometown."},"et":{"ABT 1346–":"umbes 1346–Surnud","1346–Male":"1346–Surnud","1343–Female":"1343–Surnud","1369–1414":"1369–1414","1387–Male":"1387–Surnud","1387–Female":"1387–Surnud","1329–Male":"1329–Surnud","1333–Female":"1333–Surnud","1414":"1414","1369":"1369","1346":"1346","1355":"1355","1333":"1333","about 1369":"umbes 1369","1387":"1387","1343":"1343","ABT 1346":"umbes 1346","abt.1387":"umbes 1387","abt 1387":"umbes 1387","1329":"1329",",, England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Thinghill, Hereford, England":"Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Thinghill, Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Herefordshire, England":"Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Thinghill, Hereford, Eng.":"Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Withington, Herefordshire, England":"Withington, Herefordshire, England"},"fi":{"ABT 1346–":"noin 1346–Kuollut","1346–Male":"1346–Kuollut","1343–Female